title: SS.PT.385
prompt: If in the year 2050, the mean center of the U.S. population moved to the western-most end of Kentucky, which of the following would be true? Chose the best answer.
description: The map shows the mean center of population for the United States from 1790 to 2000.
feedback: The mean, or average, center of population is closer to areas where the population is higher. The farther east the mean center of population is, the higher the population in the East is compared to the population in the West. If the mean center of the population in 2050 were in Kentucky, the population would still be, generally, moving south, but there would be a higher concentration of population in the East than in 2000. This could be explained if the population in the East increased faster than the population in the West.
